## 5. What is an IDE?

### Definition
An **IDE (Integrated Development Environment)** is a software application that provides comprehensive tools for software development in one place.

### Core Components of an IDE

| Component | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Code Editor** | Write and edit source code with syntax highlighting |
| **Compiler/Interpreter** | Translate code into executable programs |
| **Debugger** | Find and fix errors step-by-step |
| **Build Automation** | Automate tasks like compiling and testing |
| **Version Control Integration** | Git operations inside the IDE |
| **IntelliSense / Autocomplete** | Smart code suggestions |
| **Terminal** | Run commands without leaving the IDE |
| **Extensions/Plugins** | Add extra functionality |

### Popular IDEs

| IDE | Language/Use |
|---|---|
| **VS Code** | Universal (most popular) |
| **IntelliJ IDEA** | Java, Kotlin |
| **PyCharm** | Python |
| **Eclipse** | Java |
| **Xcode** | Swift / iOS / macOS |
| **Android Studio** | Android (Java/Kotlin) |
| **WebStorm** | JavaScript/TypeScript |

