## 6. Installing Visual Studio Code

### What is VS Code?
Visual Studio Code (VS Code) is a **free, open-source, lightweight IDE** by Microsoft. It supports virtually every programming language through extensions.

### Installation Steps

#### Windows
1. Go to [https://code.visualstudio.com](https://code.visualstudio.com)
2. Click **"Download for Windows"**
3. Run the `.exe` installer
4. Follow setup wizard → check **"Add to PATH"**
5. Launch VS Code

#### macOS
1. Go to [https://code.visualstudio.com](https://code.visualstudio.com)
2. Click **"Download for Mac"**
3. Extract the `.zip` and move `Visual Studio Code.app` to **Applications**
4. Launch from Applications or Spotlight

#### Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install wget gpg
wget -qO- https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | gpg --dearmor > packages.microsoft.gpg
sudo install -o root -g root -m 644 packages.microsoft.gpg /etc/apt/trusted.gpg.d/
sudo sh -c 'echo "deb [arch=amd64] https://packages.microsoft.com/repos/vscode stable main" > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/vscode.list'
sudo apt update
sudo apt install code
```

### Essential VS Code Extensions

